   VERSION=( "20060213" )
  CATEGORY="disk utility"
 ATTRIBUTE="console"
    SOURCE="prelink-$VERSION.tar.bz2"
       URL="http://people.redhat.com/jakub/prelink/"
  HOMEPAGE="http://people.redhat.com/jakub/prelink/"
       REQ="libelf"
   EXCLUDE="/etc/prelink.conf
            /etc/prelink.cache"
  ESTIMATE="640"
      DESC="prelink modifies ELFs to expedite runtime linking.

Prelinking of cast spells is automatic provided
that glibc is cast or prelinked following
the initial install of prelink.
glibc must be prelinked first, because
nearly all ELFs link with glibc libraries.
ELFs can only be prelinked when the
ELF libraries that they require are already prelinked.

# augur prelink
The above displays prelinked spells

# augur prelink \$SPELL
The above attempts to prelink the installed spell.

# cast \$SPELL
The above, if it compiles the spell,
will also attempt to prelink it.

If you invoke the prelink executable directly
instead of using the sorcery tools
then expect md5sum failures on installed spells."

build()  {
  default_build  &&
  touch  /etc/prelink.conf
}
